=========
linux.py
=========


What
-------------

linux.py is a python script to decrypt *nix machine user account password using Dictionary based attack.
[[ a simple brute force on /etc/shadow file ]]


Requirements
-------------

    - python 2.6+ <http://www.python.org>
      (older version before 2.5 aren't recommended)

Linux Debian/Ubuntu:

    sudo aptitude install python
    
    
Portability
-------------

This is developed and tested mostly on Linux, though it should support others posix systems.


Usage
-------------

    # python linux.py -f /etc/shadow
    Please enter the dictionary file path = <enter dictionary file path>



Don't hesitate to reports bugs and submit patches, or just mail author.
